text: Parliamentary elections were held in Estonia on 3 March 2019. The newly elected 101 members of the 14th Riigikogu assembled at Toompea Castle in Tallinn within ten days of the election. The Reform Party remained the largest party, winning four seats for a total of 34 and the Conservative People's Party had the largest gain overall, increasing their seat count by 12 to a total of 19 seats. ==References== Category:2019 elections in Europe Category:Elections in Estonia Category:2010s in Estonia Category:March 2019 events
title: 2019 Estonian parliamentary election
